# .clinerules

# Project: vdi_wrapper
# Description: This file documents the high‑level code structure and the
# responsibilities of each component in the VDI wrapper project.

# 1. include/vdi_client.h
#    - Provides the VdiClient class interface.
#    - On Windows builds includes <windows.h>, <vdi.h>, and <combaseapi.h>.
#    - Defines a placeholder implementation for non‑Windows platforms to allow
#      compilation without the actual VDI SDK.
#    - Exposes:
#        * IClientVirtualDeviceSet2* device_set_;
#        * bool connect(const std::wstring&, int);
#        * Destructor releases COM object and calls CoUninitialize() on Windows.

# 2. src/vdi_client.cpp
#    - Implements VdiClient.
#    - Windows path:
#        * Calls CoInitializeEx(COINIT_MULTITHREADED).
#        * Uses CoCreateInstance to obtain CLSID_MSSQL_ClientVirtualDeviceSet.
#        * Configures VDConfig and calls device_set_->CreateEx().
#        * Returns true on success.
#    - Non‑Windows path:
#        * Returns true as a stub.

# 3. include/backup_request.h
#    - Defines BackupRequest struct with database name, backup type,
#      device count, buffer size, and device name.

# 4. include/backup_engine.h / src/backup_engine.cpp
#    - BackupEngine orchestrates a backup session.
#    - start_backup():
#        * Creates a VdiClient instance.
#        * Calls client->connect() with request parameters.
#        * Creates a NullSink (placeholder sink implementation).
#        * Constructs BackupSession with the client and sink.
#        * Runs the session.

# 5. src/main.cpp
#    - Entry point for the application.
#    - Constructs a BackupRequest, sets database and type.
#    - Instantiates BackupEngine and starts the backup.

# 6. include/sqlvdi_guids.h
#    - Declares CLSID_MSSQL_ClientVirtualDeviceSet and IID_IClientVirtualDeviceSet2
#      using EXTERN_C const with <guiddef.h>.
#    - Can be included from any file that needs these GUID symbols.

# 7. src/sqlvdi_guids.cpp
#    - Defines the GUIDs via DEFINE_GUID() under #define INITGUID.
#    - Only file in the project that ever #defines INITGUID, preventing
#      multiple-definition linker errors.
#    - Replaces the old sqlvdi.cpp which used brace initialization instead
#      of the standard Windows DEFINE_GUID/INITGUID pattern.

# 8. CMakeLists.txt
#    - Sets C++17 standard.
#    - Includes the 'include' directory.
#    - Builds the vdi_wrapper executable from the source files:
#        * src/main.cpp
#        * src/vdi_client.cpp
#        * src/backup_engine.cpp
#        * src/backup_session.cpp
#        * src/sink.cpp
#        * src/sqlvdi_guids.cpp     (was sqlvdi.cpp prior to GUID refactor)
#    - Links against ole32.lib (required for COM on Windows).

# 9. Build notes
#    - On Windows, the project must be built with a compiler that can locate
#      the VDI SDK headers (vdi.h) and libraries.
#    - On non‑Windows platforms the placeholder definitions allow the code to
#      compile, but the VDI functionality will be a no‑op.

# 10. GUID Architecture (refactored 2026-05-09)
#     - GUIDs are declared in include/sqlvdi_guids.h (EXTERN_C const with <guiddef.h>)
#       and defined in src/sqlvdi_guids.cpp (single #define INITGUID + DEFINE_GUID).
#     - This avoids:
#         * Multiple-definition linker errors (only one .cpp ever defines INITGUID)
#         * Header pollution (consumers only see extern declarations)
#         * Fragile brace-initialization (the old sqlvdi.cpp approach)
#     - GUID values:
#         CLSID_MSSQL_ClientVirtualDeviceSet = {0x40700425,0x0080,0x11d2,{0x85,0x1f,0x00,0xc0,0x4f,0xc2,0x17,0x59}}
#         IID_IClientVirtualDeviceSet2        = {0x40700425,0x0080,0x11d2,{0x85,0x1f,0x00,0xc0,0x4f,0xc2,0x17,0x59}}

# 11. VDI COM Registration Test
#     - Confirmed (2026-05-09): CLSID_MSSQL_ClientVirtualDeviceSet
#       ({40700425-0080-11d2-851f-00c04fc21759}) IS registered on this machine.
#       CoCreateInstance returns SUCCESS.
#     - Compilation commands (MSVC x64, run from repo root):
#       $env:Path = "C:\Program Files\Microsoft Visual Studio\18\Community\VC\Tools\MSVC\14.50.35717\bin\Hostx64\x64;" + $env:Path;
#       $env:INCLUDE = "C:\Program Files\Microsoft Visual Studio\18\Community\VC\Tools\MSVC\14.50.35717\include;C:\Program Files (x86)\Windows Kits\10\Include\10.0.26100.0\ucrt;C:\Program Files (x86)\Windows Kits\10\Include\10.0.26100.0\um;C:\Program Files (x86)\Windows Kits\10\Include\10.0.26100.0\shared;C:\Users\azureuser\source\repos\rushikesh90\vdi-cpp-wrapper\include";
#       $env:LIB = "C:\Program Files\Microsoft Visual Studio\18\Community\VC\Tools\MSVC\14.50.35717\lib\x64;C:\Program Files (x86)\Windows Kits\10\Lib\10.0.26100.0\ucrt\x64;C:\Program Files (x86)\Windows Kits\10\Lib\10.0.26100.0\um\x64";
#       cl src\sqlvdi_guids.cpp /c /EHsc /std:c++17 /Fosqlvdi_guids.obj   # GUID definition compile test
#       cl src\vdi_client.cpp /c /EHsc /std:c++17 /Fovdi_client.obj       # Consumer compile test
#     - Key detail: only the single definition file (sqlvdi_guids.cpp) places
#       `#define INITGUID` BEFORE any includes; all other files consume the
#       EXTERN_C const declarations from sqlvdi_guids.h without INITGUID.

# End of .clinerules
